===Adjective===
'''rocky'''

#Full of, or abounding in, [[rock]]s; consisting of rocks; as, a rocky mountain; a rocky shore.
#Like a rock; as, the rocky orb of a shield.
#(''Figurative'') Not easily impressed or affected; [[hard]]; [[unfeeling]]; [[obdurate]]; as, a rocky bosom.
#(''Figurative'') [[troubled|Troubled]]; or [[difficult]]; in [[danger]] or [[distress]].
#:''Their relationship had weathered some '''rocky''' times, but they loved each other.''
#Unstable; easily [[rocked]].
#:''The table was rocky, so we put a book under one leg.''

